== About the Lab

The research group is led by [index.html Dr. Alberto Padoan].

We are hosted by the [https://ece.ubc.ca/ Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering] at the [https://www.ubc.ca/ University of British Columbia] on [https://maps.app.goo.gl/q62rQSVnjRkCs2Ft8 Point Grey campus], located on the unceded lands of the xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam) people. 

Nestled between forests, mountains, and the ocean, [https://maps.app.goo.gl/CdtmBHU1NEw7SNYy8 Vancouver] is consistently celebrated as one of the most [https://worldpopulationreview.com/world-city-rankings/most-diverse-city-in-the-world diverse] and [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/City_quality_of_life_indices livable] cities worldwide.

The lab offers a vibrant and inclusive environment to develop expertise in control, optimization, and computing while addressing meaningful engineering challenges.


== Join us

*Qualifications*

- A Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in mathematics, physics, engineering, or a related field.
- Strong communication and interpersonal skills.
- Completion of an introductory course in control systems.
- Above all, a passion for learning and a growth-oriented mindset.

*How to apply*\n
Email the following documents to apadoan \[@\] ece \[DOT\] ubc \[DOT\] ca

- Your resume/CV.
- A cover letter highlighting relevant experience and research interests.
- Transcripts of records.

*Guidelines*
- Combine all documents into a single .pdf file.
- Use the subject line: "\[UBC Application\]: LastName, FirstName".


*Notes* 
- Applications that do not follow submission guidelines will not be considered.
- Given the large number of speculative emails, only shortlisted candidates may be contacted for an online interview. 



